  "prompt": "Can I send 500 and 1000 rs cash notes to India through USPS mail from USA?",
  "response": "Sending cash through the mail, including USPS, is generally not recommended and may not be allowed due to regulations and security concerns. In the case of sending Indian currency (like 500 and 1000 rupee notes), it's important to note that these denominations might have restrictions or might not be legal to send due to various regulations.\n\nSpecifically, sending cash internationally often violates postal regulations, and there are laws regarding the transportation of currency across borders. It is advisable to consider alternatives such as wire transfers, money transfer services (like Western Union or PayPal), or using bank services to send money to India.\n\nFor detailed and specific advice, it's best to check with USPS or consult the official customs regulations, as well as any financial regulations in both the USA and India.",
